all_definitions.name: Cosmetic condition
all_definitions.description: Defines the wear and condition of electronics, e.g. new, opened-never used

all_definitions.name: SIM card capability
all_definitions.description: Indicates the type of SIM card configuration in mobile devices, e.g. dual, embedded

all_definitions.name: Operating system
all_definitions.description: Defines the system software a device uses, such as iOS or ChromeOS

all_definitions.name: Color
all_definitions.description: Defines the primary color or pattern, such as blue or striped

all_definitions.name: Subscription type
all_definitions.description: Specifies the type of subscription, typically for mobile devices; e.g. pay as you go, pre-paid

all_definitions.name: Data network
all_definitions.description: Specifies the data network compatibility of mobile devices, like LTE or 3G

all_definitions.name: Memory technology
all_definitions.description: Specifies the type of memory used in electronic devices, such as DDR or SDRAM

all_definitions.name: Storage types supported
all_definitions.description: Defines compatible storage systems for electronics, e.g. Hard disk drive (HDD)

all_definitions.name: Processor family
all_definitions.description: Identifies the series or brand of the electronic device's CPU, e.g. Intel Core i7

all_definitions.name: Connection type
all_definitions.description: Specifies the type of connection used by electronics, such as wired or Bluetooth

all_definitions.name: Computer form
all_definitions.description: Defines the physical design or layout of a computer, such as all-in-one or notebook

all_definitions.name: Graphics card type
all_definitions.description: Specifies the type of graphics card in a computer, e.g. professional, dedicated

all_definitions.name: Computer specialized features
all_definitions.description: Highlights specific computer features, like liquid cooling system or RGB lighting

all_definitions.name: Condition
all_definitions.description: Describes the state or quality of a product, e.g. mint (M), poor (P)

all_definitions.name: Keyboard type
all_definitions.description: Specifies the design and functionality of a keyboard, e.g. standard, backlit

all_definitions.name: Language version
all_definitions.description: Specifies the language version of a media product, such as ENG-US or ARA- Arabic
